➜  cipher git:(master) ✗ ./cipher.out
USAGE: ./cipher.out -f <filename> [options]

OPTIONS:
    -f, --file            File to do operations on.
    -e, --encrypt <msg>        Encrypts <msg> and saves it in file.
    -d, --decrypt        Decrypts the message loaded from file.

➜  cipher git:(master) ✗ ./cipher.out -f file -e helloworld
➜  cipher git:(master) ✗ ./cipher.out -f file -d
HELLOWORLD
➜  cipher git:(master) ✗ ./cipher.out -f file -e goodmorningjasonjames
➜  cipher git:(master) ✗ ./cipher.out -f file -d
GOODMORNINGJASONJAMES